rComments: So caring and committed to your learning. She encourages participation and the two hours just fly by. You do need to study outside of class (it's a language course, after all), but she takes the time to drill in the pronunciation, and she makes sure that everyone is on the same page. So sweet, always so put together.

Prof is great- she's really funny, understanding, and fair. Makes learning Russian way more fun. Kinda disorganized though, but that is part of her character. I wouldn't have had nearly as good of a time in that class if not for her.
best prof ever. teaches you a language in 4 months.

Amazing professor! Really helpful and takes a genuine interest in teaching students. Teaching Russian is just as hard as learning it but she makes it enjoyable. However, to do well you really have to commit to doing all the work she assigns.
